        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(vydra,xai,runway,pixverse,deepinfra,together,elevenlabs,microsoft): bound JSON response reads to prevent OOM",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nReplace unbounded `await response.json()` with `readResponseWithLimit` (1 MiB cap)\nacross 8 provider extensions — the symmetric counterpart to bound-stream work\nalready merged in #95420 (OpenRouter), #95417 (Google), #95218 (provider-http),\nand the same pattern applied in #96321-#96324.\n\nA malicious or faulty API endpoint returning an oversized JSON response body would\npreviously buffer the entire body in memory before parsing. `readResponseWithLimit`\ncancels the stream once the cap is reached, preventing unbounded buffering.\n\n## Changes\n\n- **`extensions/vydra/video-generation-provider.ts`** — bound JSON submit response\n- **`extensions/vydra/speech-provider.ts`** — bound JSON payload response\n- **`extensions/vydra/image-generation-provider.ts`** — bound JSON submit response\n- **`extensions/xai/xai-oauth.ts`** — bound OAuth token JSON responses (2 call sites)\n- **`extensions/xai/stt.ts`** — bound STT JSON response\n- **`extensions/runway/video-generation-provider.ts`** — bound JSON response read\n- **`extensions/pixverse/video-generation-provider.ts`** — bound JSON response read\n- **`extensions/deepinfra/video-generation-provider.ts`** — bound JSON status response\n- **`extensions/together/video-generation-provider.ts`** — bound JSON submit response\n- **`extensions/elevenlabs/speech-provider.ts`** — bound voice list JSON response\n- **`extensions/microsoft-foundry/image-generation-provider.ts`** — bound image response\n- **`extensions/microsoft/speech-provider.ts`** — bound voice list JSON response\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Follows the same bounded-read + `JSON.parse` pattern established by prior\n  fixes in this repo (#95420, #95417, #95218, #96321-#96324)\n- Several of these modules already use `readResponseWithLimit` for media\n  downloads (runway, together) — this extends coverage to JSON response paths\n- 1 MiB cap is safe for metadata-level JSON responses (voice lists, OAuth tokens,\n  video status/submit payloads)",
